Class MinFilter

java.lang.Object
  Filter
      MinFilter

public class MinFilter
extends Filter

This #Filter subclass will determine the minimum input #Signal from the set of previous inputs and that #Signal will be the output of this filter.

Author:
StevePaley

Creates a new instance of a MinFilter that will return the minimum input from within the given window size (the n previous inputs).

Parameters:
windowSize - The number of previous inputs to check in for the minimum from. If the input is negative, take the absolute value. Passing zero acts the same as the no parameter constructor.
